<p>No, you are not.</p>

<p>You should use the package management available on your operating system. If your software is in <code>tar.gz</code> format, you should re-package it locally as <code>.deb</code>, <code>.rpm</code> or whatever.</p>

<p>If the software is something developed locally, you should use whatever build/deploy tools are available for it.</p>
