<p>You might want to try using <a href="https://github.com/jordansissel/fpm#readme">fpm</a> to make RPMs or DEBs of your tarballs; it's really simple to use, and you don't have to understand anything about the package formats you don't want to.</p>

<p>To answer your original question, the right way to deploy applications with Puppet is to make Puppet do as little work as possible; any complicated <code>exec</code> resources that download and extract tarballs are bound to be very, very brittle, and making Puppet just <code>yum install</code> a package is much healthier long-run.</p>
